& [SLMSlice32ImperativeSubjectImpliedActor] is a work-ready slice for command subject uncertainty
  + [slice_id] is SLM-32
  + [status] is verified_wsl
  + [effort] is M
  + [risk] is medium
  + [depends_on] is SLM-20, SLM-24, SLM-31
  + [scope] is represent command-like inputs with implied actor or command subject uncertainty
  + [deliverable] is diffusion rule and uncertainty proposal for imperative subject boundaries
  + [acceptance_criteria] is "Design a compiler for FPGA hardware." can preserve implied actor uncertainty without making "compiler" the grammatical subject
  + [proof_route] is WSL cargo test plus demo primer inspection
  + [exclusions] is full imperative grammar parser
  + [next_action] is refine implied actor only when downstream sidecar/provider evidence can propose a concrete actor

  ! [CompletionEvidence] is the SLM-32 verification record
